1.2. Rich Dialogs
1.2.1. ch.ivyteam.ivy.addons.filemanager
1.2.1.1. FileManagerOverride
Panel Class
FileManagerOverridePanel
Interface
Start Methods
* startAsPathChooser(String)
start the RDC as Path chooser. The user will be able to make a new directory, no actions on Files are possible.
start with the pathChooserFlowLayout visible, the other buttons are not visible.
By clicking on the OK button, the RDC gives the choosed path back, else, empty string.
* startWithServerPathAndIvyDbConnectionNameAndDbTableNameAndDBSchemaName(String,String,String,String)
Application start with serverPath/IvyDBConnectionName/DBTableName/DBSchemaName*.
The server path is the root directory in the server file system.
the IvyDBConnectionName is the name of the Ivy Database Connection configuration. Per default "FileManager"
The DBTableName is the Table name where the files informations are going to be stored. Per Default "UPLOADEDFILES"
*This parameter is only supported for PostgreSQL. It indicates the schemata that contains the table. Default is "public".
* startWithServerPathAndIvyDbConnectionNameAndDbTableName(String,String,String)
Application start with serverPath/IvyDBConnectionName/DBTableName.
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
the IvyDBConnectionName is the name of the Ivy Database Connection configuration, used to store the files informations. Per default "FileManager"
The DBTableName is the Table name where the files informations are going to be stored. Per Default "UPLOADEDFILES"
* startWithServerPathAndWithClientTempDirAndShowTree(String,String,Boolean)
Application start mit serverPath, ClientTempDir, ApplicationContext and show Tree. 
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
ClientTempDir: This is the File Temporary Directory at Client side. Used for automatic download,
like ones for File edit.
ApplicationContext Object for Application settings like XHRM UserID.
Boolean ShowTree: the visibility propertie of the Directory TreePane.
* startWithServerPath(String)
Application start with serverPath.
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
The IvyConnexion Name has to be "FileManager", the table has to be "UPLOADEDFILES".

* start()
Default Rich Dialog start
This method can not be changed or deleted!
* startWithServerPathAndFileManagementHandlerAndIsRecursiveAndShowTree(String,ch.ivyteam.ivy.addons.filemanager.database.AbstractFileManagementHandler,Boolean,Boolean)
Application start with serverPath and isRecursive and ApplicationContext and show Tree. 
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
A FileManagementHandler extends AbstractFileManagementHandler
isRecursive: if true the documents are searched recursively under the serverpath.
ApplicationContext Object for Application settings like XHRM UserID.
Boolean ShowTree: the visibility propertie of the Directory TreePane.
* startWithServerPathAndFileManagementHandler(String,ch.ivyteam.ivy.addons.filemanager.database.AbstractFileManagementHandler)
Application start with serverPath. 
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
A FileManagementHandler is an Object that has to extend the AbstractFileManagementHandler. It is responsible for storing the File indexation from
the files on the server. The indexation system contains all the properties available for the files like file Id, File name, creation user, locked if there is any locking system...
* startWithServerPathAndIsRecursiveAndShowTree(String,Boolean,Boolean)
Application start with serverPath and isRecursive and ApplicationContext and show Tree. 
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
isRecursive: if true the documents are searched recursively under the serverpath.
ApplicationContext Object for Application settings like XHRM UserID.
Boolean ShowTree: the visibility propertie of the Directory TreePane.
* startAsPathChooserWithIvySystemDb(String)
start the RDC as Path chooser. The user will be able to make a new directory, no actions on Files are possible.
start with the pathChooserFlowLayout visible, the other buttons are not visible.
By clicking on the OK button, the RDC gives the choosed path back, else, empty string.
Here the Filemanager Table is automatically created and located into the Ivy System Db
* startWithServerPathAndShowTree(String,Boolean)
Application start mit serverPath and ApplicationContext and show Tree. 
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
ApplicationContext Object for Application settings like XHRM UserID.
Boolean ShowTree: the visibility propertie of the Directory TreePane.
* startWithServerPathAndUseIvySystemDB(String)
Application start with serverPath.
The server path is the root directory in the server file system where the documents are going to be uploaded and found.
The DB Table containing the informations about the Files is located into the Ivy System Database.
* startAsPathChooserWithDBInformations(String,String,String,String)
start the RDC as Path chooser with the db Informations (ivy user friendly connexion name, Table name and schema name). 
The user will be able to make a new directory, no actions on Files are possible.
start with the pathChooserFlowLayout visible, the other buttons are not visible.
By clicking on the OK button, the RDC gives the choosed path back, else, empty string.
Methods
* getLastFileUploaded():File
get the last Uploaded File reference.
WARNING: Please check for null incomimg parameter, the File can be null.
* editFile(File):void
Tries to open a selected file in edit mode.
If the file is locked, the user will be informed that the File is going to be open in "Read only" modus.
Read only doesn't mean, that the user cannot edit and save the file on his computer, but that the changes are not going to be uploaded on the server.
If the File cannot be edited on the User's computer (like a PDF if no PDF Editor is installed), the file will be open in read only modus.

* setToolBarVisible(Boolean):void
set the toolbar visibility
* _moveFile(String,ArrayList):void
Callback Method that is called after a DnD from one or more documents
from the documents table to the ordners tree.
* setFileManagementHandler(AbstractFileManagementHandler):void
Set the FileManahgementHandler.
A FileManagementHandler is an Object that has to extend the AbstractFileManagementHandler. It is responsible for storing the File indexation from
the files on the server. The indexation system contains all the properties available for the files like file Id, File name, creation user, locked if there is any locking system...
The AbstractFileManagementHandler contains getInstance() methods to build such Objects easily.
* _deleteSelectedDirectory():void
This method is called whenever the user presses the delete Key and the Directory RTree is in FOCUS.
The Directory RTree registers to the delete keyborad action.
This method will send the deleteSelectedFolder application asynchronous event
The methods called by keyboard Events send APP events if they need to interact with the user through synchrone Windows.
* getServerPath():String
returns the serverPath.
Note: the serverPath can be different from the selectedDirectoryPath. It is the root directory
that contains all the directories that can be selected. The user cannot navigate outside the serverPath.
the serverPath is always the root from the selectedDirectoryPath
* showTree(Boolean):void
Allows to hide or show the directories Tree
* _onChangeFile(ReturnedMessage):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileUploadHandler Object to call the RDProcess back, when a File that already exists on the server
was chosen for Upload. The RDProcess can warn the user.
To be able to call this method back, the FileUploadHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setAskForChangeFileMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc. 
* _copyFiles():void
called by the CTRL+V keyboard Event
* _onProgressWithText(String):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileHandler to call the RDProcess back, when an action is in progress.
It allows you to show the progress of the current operation.It gives the indicated text performed back.
To be able to call this method back, the FileHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setSuccessMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc. 
* setSelectedFile(File):void
If the file is present in the list of displayed DocumentOnServer Objects, the RTable will select the given java.io.File.
* _pasteFiles():void
Called by the CTRL+V key Envent. It sends the pasteFiles(panelID)@APP broadcastEvent.
This event is catched within the same FileManger and performs the rest of the Paste process.
It is necessary to go through a broadcast event here, because the paste process may display a modal dialog in some cases.

* getUserTempDirectoryPath():String
Returns the user temp directory. It should be the one from the userSystemProperties Extension.
* isFileLocked(File):Boolean
Returns true if the File is locked, else false
* _onSuccess(ReturnedMessage):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileUploadHandler Object to call the RDProcess back, when an action succeed.
The Object returned is a ReturnedMessage dataclass Object.
To be able to call this method back, the FileUploadHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setSuccessMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc. 
* deleteDirectory(String):ReturnedMessage
Delete the directory designed by the given path only if the directory is empty (no files, no other directories).
Cannot delete the actual workking directory root (in.serverPath variable)
Return ReturnedMessage Object with the success status.
* getSelectedDocuments():List<DocumentOnServer>
Returns the selected documents in the File Table.
returns a List<DocumentOnServer>
* addFiles(List<File>):void
Add a list of Files into the Db and into the documents table list.
It doesn't check if the files are really presents on the server.
This check is performed with the next refresh action.
* mail(List<String>,List<String>,List<String>,String,String,Boolean,List<File>):void
tries to open the default user mail program to mail the selected documents.
Following parameters:
to : List<String>: the list of email addresses of the primary receivers of the email (separated by a coma)
cc :  List<String>: the list of email addresses of receivers in copy (separated by a coma)
bcc:  List<String>: the list of email addresses of receivers in invisible copy(separated by a coma)

* getSelectedDirectoryPath():String
Returns the selected directory path
* _onError(ReturnedMessage):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileUploadHandler Object to call the RDProcess back, when an error occured.
The Object returned is a ReturnedMessage dataclass Object.
To be able to call this method back, the FileUploadHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setErrorMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc. 
* _onChangeFile(File,String):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileUploadHandler Object to call the RDProcess back, when a File that already exists on the server
was chosen for Upload. The RDProcess can warn the user.
To be able to call this method back, the FileUploadHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setAskForChangeFileMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc. 
* _renameFile():void
Called by the F2 key Event on focused files Table. It sends the renameFiles(panelID)@APP broadcastEvent.
This event is catched within the same FileManger and performs the rest of the Rename process.
It is necessary to go through a broadcast event here, because the rename process displays a modal dialog (FileNameDialog).
* selectFolderOnServer(String):FolderOnServer
This method select the Folder that corresponds to the given path.
Input: String path of the folder to select
Output: the FolderOnserver Object that is selected
The Treeview selects and Scrolls to the Tree Node that corresponds to this path.It refreshes the table File list.
* getFileManagementHandler():AbstractFileManagementHandler
returns the FileManagementHandler used in the updownload panel.
A FileManagementHandler is an Object that has to extend the AbstractFileManagementHandler. It is responsible for storing the File indexation from
the files on the server. The indexation system contains all the properties available for the files like file Id, File name, creation user, locked if there is any locking system...
The AbstractFileManagementHandler contains getInstance() methods to build such Objects easily.
* setIsRecursive(Boolean):void
Set how the files are searched in the Db and the FileSystem.
If true the files are searched recursively under the selected directory.
If false, just the files directly under the directory are shown.
* _getUploadedFileFromUploadHandler(ReturnedMessage):void
Not for use from outside.
It is a callback method for the FileUploadHandler Object.
This method is called back, when a File Upload occured succesfully.
It allows the RDProcess finishing the upload process (status label, refresh of the the table...)

* makeDirectory(String):ReturnedMessage
Creates a new directory. 
The String parameter is the name of the directoy, not the entire path.
The path of the new directory is going to be the in.serverPath+name.
Use the setServerPath method to change this path.
@return a ReturnedMessage Object containing the message Type(SUCCESS==1, ERROR==2) 
and the message text
* _askIfOverwriteExistingFiles(List<File>,List<File>):void
intern callback method
used in DnD events to ask the user if some existing Files should be overwritten.
* addDocuments(List<DocumentOnServer>):void
Add a list of documents into the Db and into the documents table list.
It doesn't check if the files are really presents on the server.
This check is performed with the next refresh action.
* getAdvancedActionsEnable():Boolean
returns true if the User can perform advanced actions like delete a folder or a File...
* getIsRecursive():Boolean
if true the files are searched recursively under the selected directory.
 If false, just the files directly under the directory are shown.
* deleteFiles(List<File>):ReturnedMessage
Delete the given list of files.
Return ReturnedMessage Object with the success status.
* _onUploadSuccess(List<File>):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileUploadHandler Object to call the RDProcess back, when an action succeed on a List of java.io.File..
The Object returned is a List<java.io.FIle> dataclass Object.
To be able to call this method back, the FileUploadHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setSuccessMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc.
* _close():void
If started as pathChooser called when the user presses CTRL+W or ESC.
* setServerPath(String):void
Set the server path
It is a crucial Method when you want to reset the RD with a new Path on the server.
The RDTree and the documentsList have to be rebuilt.
It is the root directory
that contains all the directories that can be selected. The user cannot navigate outside the serverPath.
the serverPath is always the root from the selectedDirectoryPath
* printFile(File):void
tries to print a file from the server on the client default printer.
uses the DesktopHandler RDC for that tasks.

* _deleteSelectedFiles():void
This method is called whenever the user presses the delete Key
Two Delete buttons register to the delete keyborad action: the delete files and the delete folder
If some files are selected, the _deleteSelectedItems will send the deleteSelectedFiles application asynchronous event
Else, the _deleteSelectedItems will send the deleteSelectedFolder application asynchronous event
The methods called by keyboard Events send APP events if they need to interact with the user through synchrone Windows.
* getSelectedDocument():DocumentOnServer
Returns the selected document in the File Table.
The object returned is a documentOnServer Object
* _checkIfFileLocked(DocumentOnServer):Boolean
For internal use
check if a File represented by a DocumentOnServer Object is locked.
Return true if locked, else false
* enableRoundCornerIconsMode(Boolean):void
* setClientTempDir(String):void
This method allows to set the client temp directory.
It should come automatically from the embedded DesktopHandler RD.
This RD gets this parameter directly from the client Java VM.
* downloadToTemp():Boolean
This method allows to download a choosed File to a temp directory on the client machine.
The temp directory can be set with the setClientTempDir methode.
* _onProgress(Number):void
FOR CALLBACK USE ONLY
This methods allows a FileHandler to call the RDProcess back, when an action is in progress.
It allows you to show the progress of the current operation.It gives the percent performed back.
To be able to call this method back, the FileHandler has to be instantiated with a reference to this method, 
or the method has to be referenced dynamically with the setSuccessMethodName method of the FileUploadHandler
See ch.xpertline.updownload.FileUploadHandler javadoc. 
* refreshActualSelectedFolder():void
refreshes just the selected directory.
No File consistancy performed.
* refresh():void
This method allows to refresh the directory List and the files List
It refreshes the UI. It checks all the File consistancy under the serverPath.
* getDocumentsListInPath(String):List<DocumentOnServer>
Returns the documents list that are under a given Path
* setAdvancedActionsEnable(Boolean):void
Set the visibility of some the Tree popupMenu Items that allows managing the directories that are in the Directories Tree.
(delete or add directories).
Default is those popupMenu Items are hidden.
* zipFiles(List<File>):ReturnedMessage
entzipped the given Files.
The user will be prompted to give the name of the created Zip Files.
* makeDirectoryWithPath(String):ReturnedMessage
Tries to make a new Directory under the selected directory in the Tree.
The name of the new directory is given as String argument.
Returns a returnedMessage.
* enableReadOnlyMode(Boolean):void
Fired Events
* SE_fileRenamed(List) @ SYSTEM
fired whenever a FIle is successfully renamed. 
Parameters: the renamed documentOnServer. 
the panel ID.
The other FileManager are going to handle this event if they are not the same Panel (panelId)
and if they currently point to the same parent directory.
* fileUploaded(-)
Tells the parent RDC that some files were successfully uploaded
* deleteSelectedFolder(Number) @ APPLICATION
this event @ APP is sent within the _deleteSelectedDirectory method.
This method is called by the keyBoard action event when theDir RTREE is in Focus and the delete key is pressed.
The FileManager will get this event (see broadcast registration) and if the event parameter is equal to his panel ID, it means that this event occured in it.
In such a case it tries to delete the selected directory.
* SE_DocumentsUnlocked(List<DocumentOnServer>) @ SYSTEM
Fired whenever the user unlock a list of documentOnServer Objects
* deleteSelectedFiles(Number) @ APPLICATION
this event @ APP is sent within the _deleteSelectedFiles method.
This method is called by the keyBoard action event when the Files Table is in Focus and the delete key is pressed.
The FileManager will get this event (see broadcast registration) and if the event parameter is equal to his panel ID, it means that this event occured in it.
In such a case it tries to delete the selected files.
* SE_DocumentsDeleted(List) @ SYSTEM
Sent whenever one user deletes some files.
The panel catches this event and refresh the table if the path is the same as the focused Directory.
* SE_FilesDeleted(List<String>) @ SYSTEM
sent when files deleted from a Directory.
Parameters: Ivy application Name, panelID as String to be able to filter the incoming events
path of the directory where the files were deleted
* SE_renameFile(Number) @ SYSTEM
* SE_fileLocked(List) @ SYSTEM
System Event sent whenever a File is locked.
This ables the other users to refresh their list.
The FileListTable sends/catches this Event too.
It sends a list of parameters: the FileManager unique PanelId Data and 
the locked DocumentOnServer Object.
* errorOccurred(ErrorUtil) @ APPLICATION
* SE_FilesUnlocked(List<File>) @ SYSTEM
Fired whenever the user unlock a list of  java.io.File
* filesCopied(Number) @ APPLICATION
@APPLICATION: Sent when the user copy some Files in the RTable.
This will inform the other FileManager Panels that can be opened in the same 
Application that some FIles coming from another FileManager can be pasted in them.
This Event sends the FileManager unique PanelId data so that only other FileManagers will accept this Event.
* pasteFiles(Number) @ APPLICATION
see the _pasteFiles method documentation
* filesDeleted(Number)
* filesAdded(Number)
Accepted Broadcasts
* SE_renameFile(Number)
See _renameFile() method documentation
* SE_fileLocked(List)
System Event catched whenever a File is locked in a FileManger or a FileListTable.
List of parameters: the FileManager/FileListTable unique PanelId Data that sent the event and 
the locked DocumentOnServer Object.
* SE_fileRenamed(List)
see documentation of SE_fileRenamed fired Event
* deleteSelectedFolder(Number)
This broadcast event is catched when the user tries to delete a directory by pressing the delete Key.
The method called back by the keyboard event calls the _deleteSelectedFolder in the panel process.
This method cannot displays the synchr. Window, asking the user if he really wants to delete the folder.
In such a case the KeyBoard action would lost the RDPanel Context resulting in a Server side Error.
As workaround the method will send deleteSelectedFolder@APP, that is asynchron.

1.3.1.1. FileManagerOverrideData
It allows organizing and managing the files present on the server (download, upload, deletion of Files, directory management etc…). It integrates the DesktopHandlerPanel Rich Dialog.
